if you are building from source, don't modify CMakeLists.txt ,
add additional build option --cmake_extra_defines CMAKE_CUDA_ARCHITECTURES='72'

also, re: the error about wheel not supported on this platform, what version of pip are you using?
the wheels conform to manylinux2014 which requires pip >= 19.3 ; it's possible your pip version may be too old.
one more suggestion. if you must use other versions of python such as 3.8 and 3.9, i've had better success using a python venv

- Thanks for you guys highly paying attention to my case! And provided me with many suggestions!
- If I built the onnxruntime from the source, it can work without using TensorRT part successfully.
- I think that I will leave the installation of onnxurntime with TRT part. Seem Onnxruntime-gpu to be able to run it. Although it still got some errors during using the onnxruntime, I think it is a different topic in this issue. I will create another issue to discuss this bug if I need after I try more different onnxruntime verisons.
- Of course, there is still an existing issue for building the onnxruntime with TensorRT. Hence, if you guys still are interested in it and wanna keep investigating on this issue, then I would like to assist you to test it more on my device. 🙂 Or you can feel free to close this issue.

Thank you for taking your time.

Best regards,
Chieh

When you see "CUDA driver version is insufficient for CUDA runtime version", please:
1. update your GPU driver to the latest.
2. reboot. Must reboot!!!

Then try it again.

Often it happened when the system was updated but haven't been rebooted.
